&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you the kind of person that thrives on providing excellent nursing care and getting the basics right?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Is making a difference to your patients important to you? Are you a reliable, hard working person?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If your answer to these questions is yes, the Staff Nurse role on AMU Ward may be right for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our patients can have complex care needs but what is common is how much they come to trust and rely on our great team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To be in this field of work you need to REALLY care. The job is very rewarding as well as demanding at times. This is a fast paced environment where no two days are the same! You will get exposure to a whole range of medical conditions, AMU is a fantastic learning environment for all nurses regardless of their previous experience. We are a 45 bedded unit which can recieve between 30 - 50 referrals a day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; In return for your hard work and commitment we offer a range of employee benefits for development and progression. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKelly SavilleJob titleSenior SisterEmail addresskelly.saville@walsallhealthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number01922 721172 ext 7541Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If anyone would like more details beforehand or to talk then please contact Kelly Saville or Kirti Kotian&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;email: kelly.saville@walsallhealthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
